    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-06-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-06-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="40"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d40">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bryan</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-06-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 19, 1901</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 244.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has been gratified to receive your
                    No. 323, of the 20th ultimo, reporting that the government of the State of Rio
                    de Janeiro has promptly settled for the damages done by the mob to the American
                    Baptist mission at Nictheroy.</p>
                <p>The course pursued by you in the matter is commended.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
